{"type":"message","id":"bebabfa5","parentId":"f46f330c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:38:28.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户问这个提醒是否与飞书关联。让我分析一下：\n\n1. 当前会话是通过飞书（Feishu）进行的，从 inbound context 可以看到 channel 和 provider 都是 \"feishu\"\n2. 我使用 `--channel last` 参数，这意味着提醒会发送到最后一次交互的渠道\n3. 由于用户是通过飞书与我对话的，\"last\" 渠道应该就是飞书\n\n所以我可以确认这个提醒会通过飞书发送给用户。\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n是的，这个提醒会通过飞书发送给你 📱\n\n我用了 `--channel last` 参数，它会把提醒发送到你最后交互的渠道。因为你是在飞书里跟我对话的，所以提醒会直接发到飞书。\n\n到时到点（明天 10:30），飞书会收到这条消息：\n> ⏰ 会议提醒：您有一个会议在 10:30 开始"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":6,"output":202,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":15881,"totalTokens":16089,"cost":{"input":6.6e-7,"output":0.00005656,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00005722}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775025503735,"responseId":"msg_b2138a90-84a1-4365-b8dd-62b2708f229c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4895cde8","parentId":"bebabfa5","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:39:40.076Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b53ff94bb1884c4d8dfca0a0f594\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-01 14:39 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b53ff94bb1884c4d8dfca0a0f594]\nou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc: 为什么这个群 oc\\_3d6ebd5cb41d4cf5847b8b2babedd07d说会议提醒，你会回答说我目前没有访问日历或提醒工具的权限，无法直接帮你创建会议提醒。\n你可以："}],"timestamp":1775025580075}}
{"type":"message","id":"421df6ca","parentId":"4895cde8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:39:48.785Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户问为什么在另一个群聊（oc_3d6ebd5cb41d4cf5847b8b2babedd07d）中，我会回答\"没有访问日历或提醒工具的权限\"。\n\n这个群聊 ID 看起来是一个不同的会话。可能的原因：\n\n1. 那个群聊可能是多人参与的，根据 SOUL.md 的群聊规则，我应该\"只回应@提及或明确提问\"\n2. 或者那个群聊的配置不同，可能没有正确的渠道配置\n3. 或者我在那个群聊中无法确定\"last\"渠道\n\n让我检查一下当前会话和那个会话的区别。当前的会话是飞书直聊（chat_type: direct），而那个群聊可能是一个群组。\n\n实际上，用户说的是\"这个群 oc_3d6ebd5cb41d4cf5847b8b2babedd07d\"，这表明那是一个群聊。在群聊中：\n- 根据 SOUL.md，我应该在群聊中\"只回应@提及或明确提问\"\n- 但更关键的是，群聊中可能无法正确路由消息\n\n我需要向用户解释这个差异，并说明在当前这个直聊环境中是可以正常工作的。\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n好问题！那个群聊和现在的场景不同：\n\n**群聊（oc_3d6ebd5cb41d4cf5847b8b2babedd07d）：**\n- 是多人参与的群组\n- 根据我的设定，群聊中需要被 @ 才会回应\n- 群聊的渠道配置可能不同，`--channel last` 可能无法正确路由到个人\n\n**现在的直聊：**\n- 是你和我的一对一对话\n- 渠道明确是飞书私聊\n- `--channel last` 能正确追踪到你的飞书账号\n\n如果你想在群里也能收到提醒，有几种方式：\n\n1. **在群里@我** 说\"帮我订个提醒\"，我会尝试创建\n2. **指定渠道**：用 `--to` 参数明确指定你的飞书 ID\n3. **私聊处理**：像现在这样在私聊里设置提醒\n\n需要我帮你在群里也测试一下吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":6,"output":486,"cacheRead":15881,"cacheWrite":602,"totalTokens":16975,"cost":{"input":6.6e-7,"output":0.00013608,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00013674000000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775025580076,"responseId":"msg_42e44dc1-22d0-4c4b-9c56-5663de3fb22d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3cfd273","parentId":"421df6ca","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:40:55.647Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b53ff91e0eca0c32f46eefe22d21\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-01 14:40 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b53ff91e0eca0c32f46eefe22d21]\nou_45ca8d7feaddef8a7a182779a434c8bc: 那你可以直接给我做飞书日历的预约吗"}],"timestamp":1775025655646}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5d427e8","parentId":"b3cfd273","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:40:59.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户问我能否直接帮他创建飞书日历的预约/日程。\n\n让我想想 OpenClaw 是否有飞书日历的集成能力。根据我看到的技能列表，有 feishu-doc、feishu-drive、feishu-perm、feishu-wiki 等，但没有明确提到 feishu-calendar 或类似的日历技能。\n\n我应该：\n1. 检查一下是否有飞书日历相关的工具或技能\n2. 或者搜索一下 OpenClaw 的文档看是否支持飞书日历\n\n让我先搜索一下是否有飞书日历相关的技能或工具。","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_710969bf674245af8c4cc268","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw --help"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":6,"output":156,"cacheRead":16483,"cacheWrite":840,"totalTokens":17485,"cost":{"input":6.6e-7,"output":0.00004368,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00004434}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775025655647,"responseId":"msg_3b2b2d79-995a-4792-90dc-02f27e203500"}}
{"type":"message","id":"df0adbcc","parentId":"b5d427e8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:41:00.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_710969bf674245af8c4cc268","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.24 (cff6dc9) — I've seen your commit messages. We'll work on that together.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --container <name>   Run the CLI inside a running Podman/Docker container\n                       named <name> (default: env OPENCLAW_CONTAINER)\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts guided\n                       setup.\n  configure            Interactive configuration for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models\n  node *               Run and manage the headless node host service\n  nodes *              Manage gateway-owned node pairing and node commands\n  onboard              Interactive onboarding for gateway, workspace, and skills\n  pairing *            Secure DM pairing (approve inbound requests)\n  plugins *            Manage OpenClaw plugins and extensions\n  qr                   Generate iOS pairing QR/setup code\n  reset                Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox *            Manage sandbox containers for agent isolation\n  secrets *            Secrets runtime reload controls\n  security *           Security tools and local config audits\n  sessions *           List stored conversation sessions\n  setup                Initialize local config and agent workspace\n  skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":96,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.24 (cff6dc9) — I've seen your commit messages. We'll work on that together.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --container <name>   Run the CLI inside a running Podman/Docker container\n                       named <name> (default: env OPENCLAW_CONTAINER)\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts guided\n                       setup.\n  configure            Interactive configuration for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files\n  message *            Send, read, and manage messages\n  models *             Discover, scan, and configure models\n  node *               Run and manage the headless node host service\n  nodes *              Manage gateway-owned node pairing and node commands\n  onboard              Interactive onboarding for gateway, workspace, and skills\n  pairing *            Secure DM pairing (approve inbound requests)\n  plugins *            Manage OpenClaw plugins and extensions\n  qr                   Generate iOS pairing QR/setup code\n  reset                Reset local config/state (keeps the CLI installed)\n  sandbox *            Manage sandbox containers for agent isolation\n  secrets *            Secrets runtime reload controls\n  security *           Security tools and local config audits\n  sessions *           List stored conversation sessions\n  setup                Initialize local config and agent workspace\n  skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Run summary\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \"Hi\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli","cwd":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace-fox-openclaw_ai"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775025660063}}
